<item>
            <title>[HBASE-799] Deprecate all remaining methods that take Text as a parameter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-799</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-796&quot; title=&quot;Deprecates Text/String methods from HTable and modifies all classes that used Text/String methods so that they use byte[] instead&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-796&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-796&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; deprecated methods in HTable that take Text as a parameter. However there are still methods in the public API in HColumnDescriptor, HBaseAdmin, BatchUpdate that should also be deprecated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While we&apos;re at it we should deprecate all methods that take Text as a parameter.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12401807">HBASE-799</key>
            <summary>Deprecate all remaining methods that take Text as a parameter</summary>
